here, we set up the audio Feature by extracting the instruments from the audio and isolating the drums.
Then, before we convert the Feature into IPAdapter weights, we shape" the feature with the FeatureMixer to make it drive the weights in a suitable way.

This example uses an audio feature, but it could be swapped out for any of the features in the node pack, including MIDI, Depth, Color, Time, Brightness, and more

This example is meant to demonstrate modulating an IP adapter with the Feature system introduced by the ryanontheinside nodes.

For this example, we will simply apply an IPAdapter to the background of a video, controlled by the drums in a song.
